Zduny  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Małdyty, within Ostróda County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north of Małdyty,  north-west of Ostróda, and  north-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
